Welcome back to a jam-packed What I=E2=80=99m Hearing that contains
exactly zero Blake Lively or Justin Baldoni. Here in L.A., I think we=E2=80=
=99re all still pretty consumed by the fire aftermath. Even as winds die do=
wn and evacuation orders lift, air quality is still a preoccupation. (I=E2=
=80=99ve been using this site ( https://www.iqair.com/us/usa/california/los=
-angeles?srsltid=3DAfmBOoo3GFar0VrKtR8Zut_pJq0yRpHzq35YIfc4T8QKuj6RDuxkzqp4=
&utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F16%2F25%29&utm_cont=
ent=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F16%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail=
_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) to monitor=
 particulates.) Amid
it all, Hollywood chugs along. To that end, Academy voters: Don=E2=80=99t f=
orget to fill out your Oscar ballots by 5 p.m. tomorrow.

=C2=A0

Reflecting this weird moment, tonight I=E2=80=99ve got some original report=
ing on Netflix=E2=80=99s big Greta Gerwig movie, Ben Stiller=E2=80=99s cost=
 overruns on Severance, and what might end up being the movie flop of the y=
