 Man</em>, the disastrous <strong>Robbie Williams</strong> biopic starring =
a CGI chimpanzee that somehow cost $110 million to produce and opened to ju=
st $1 million domestic in 1,200 theaters. Gracey (<em>The Greatest Showman<=
/em>) is one of six main investors cobbled together by producer <strong>Pau=
l Currie</strong>, CAA Media Finance, and
Australia=E2=80=99s Elevate Production Finance, including the Victorian gov=
ernment there. It=E2=80=99s unclear <em>how much</em> Gracey contributed to=
 the R-rated anthropomorphic chimp pic (his rep declined to comment), but w=
e know Paramount burnt $25 million on North American rights, in part becaus=
e the studio is developing another, presumably more commercial movie with G=
racey, <em>Nevermoor</em>. And <strong>Nigel Green</strong>=E2=80=99s Enter=
tainment Film Distributors, which released the film in the U.K., where
